Excellent, I have been making coeur a la creme for Easter for over 35 years. Decided to look for another recipe. Have made this two times in the last month and will make it for Easter.I used a package of frozen raspberries for the sauce then added fresh berries around the mold.

Rating: 4
Easy to make and delicious! Have made it often and always use the perforated mold. For the "Cook From Ottawa" these dishes are available at the Domus store downtown for a very reasonable price. I now use a raspberry sauce by The Black Bear Fruit Company made here in B.C. and available at Loblaws stores,etc. Certainly saves that tedious step of straining the seeds in the raspberry sauce. This recipe from Epicurious is excellent. A friend's recipe substitutes the Mascarpone Cheese with a mixture of cottage cheese and cream cheese whipped together but I prefer the taste and texture of the Mascarpone which is available at Farm Boy Stores here in Ottawa..less expensive than other stores. I have traveled with this dessert in a cooler for hours, unmolding it when dinner is served later that day.

